      <bioghist id="aspace_ee46074af91aafd80fd021e82d0f60f0">
         <head>Conrad Moricand (1887-1954)</head>
         <p>Conrad Moricand, French astrologer and author; also used the name Claude Valence.  Moricand lived with American author Henry Miller in Big Sur, California, in 1948, and was the subject of Miller's memoir <title>
               <part>A Devil in Paradise</part>
            </title> ([New York]: The New American Library, [1956]), also published in Miller's <title>
               <part>Big Sur and the Oranges of Hieronymus Bosch</part>
            </title> (New York: New Directions, 1957).</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <arrangement id="aspace_b1e6010bf98b7940f32bbdef9445c3f1">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Organized into four series: I. Correspondence, 1915-1956.  Series II. Writings, 1952 and undated.  III. Writings and Visual Materials by Others, 1950 and undated.  IV. Other Papers, 1909-1957.</p>  
      </arrangement>
